<br>
I thought the Plane of Fire quest was the beginning of openeing the other Planes, aparantly I was wrong. The Fire Drake was more than happy to give me a Character Flag, the Earth Drake spoke to me, but didn't give me a flag. The Air Drake insisted I speak to someone else before he let me in, and the Water Drake flat out ignored me.<br>
<br>
I think the Unlocking process starts in Plane of Justice, because there are a lot of NPC's there that give out quests. Theres a gnome in Plane of Tranquility that also gives a quest that goes through Justice, so that just may be the beginning.<br>
<br>
Also, lanquanges play a big role, as some NPC's in Justice do not understand Common, and will not reply unless the hail and key words are in their lanquange. I'm not sure if your need X skill to speak to them, or need X skill to understand them.<br>
<br>
I haven't explored Plane of Nightmares or Disease yet, too chicken to explore them,  but I did join a random Innovation raid, it was loads of fun, but I didn't see any Quest-like NPC's.<br>
<br>
